                </ul>
                <h4 class="mb-4">What you should have</h4>
                <ul class="What_list_num">
                    <li>At least 3 years in a leadership role managing platform / channel partnerships selling to enterprise buyers (ideally to health care / employee benefits buyers).</li>
                    <li>7+ years of experience in Sales, Account Management, Marketing, Product, Benefit Consulting, or Platform/Channel roles.</li>
                    <li>Experience with digital health, employee benefit programs, and/or software for healthcare applications.</li>
                    <li>Relationship developer, team player who will seek out and find success for both Pivot and partners for win-win solutions.</li>
                    <li>Highly organized, strategic thinker who can develop strategies, outline requirements and measure results.</li>
                    <li>Has a combination of sales, creative ideation, and team and project management skills to develop and test programs, iterate and expand.</li>
                    <li>Ability to develop business cases (qualitative and quantitative) to drive prioritization decisions and inspire teams to deliver on projects. </li>
                    <li>Excellent documentation and communication skills to keep teams and stakeholders aligned.</li>
                    <li>Experience leading cross-functional projects and teams.</li>
                    <li>Bachelor’s degree, MBA preferred.</li>
                </ul>
